TypeBrowserDialog Class

In this Article

Represents a dialog box that allows the user to choose a type. This class cannot be inherited.

Syntax

Declaration

[System.Obsolete("The System.Workflow.* types are deprecated.  Instead, please use the new types from System.Activities.*")]
public sealed class TypeBrowserDialog : System.Windows.Forms.Form, IServiceProvider, System.ComponentModel.ISite

Remarks

Note

This material discusses types and namespaces that are obsolete. For more information, see Deprecated Types in Windows Workflow Foundation 4.5.

This class prompts the user to browse a list of Windows Workflow Foundation and .NET Framework namespaces and their contained types and select a single type.

Explicit Interface Implementations

  • ISite.Component

    Gets the component to associate with the type browser dialog box.

    System.ComponentModel.IComponent System.ComponentModel.ISite.Component { get; }

    Returns

    • IComponent

      The IComponent to bind to the TypeBrowserDialog.

    Remarks

    If the property returns a valid value--anything other than a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic)--the component is added to TypeBrowserDialog.

    This property is required because TypeBrowserDialog implements ISite. For TypeBrowserDialog, <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.Component%2A> always returns a null reference (Nothing).

  • ISite.Container

    Gets the container to associate with the type browser dialog.

    System.ComponentModel.IContainer System.ComponentModel.ISite.Container { get; }

    Returns

    • IContainer

      The IContainer to associate with the TypeBrowserDialog.

    Remarks

    If <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.Container%2A> returns a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic), <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.Component%2A> has not bound an IComponent to the TypeBrowserDialog.

    This method is required because TypeBrowserDialog implements ISite. For TypeBrowserDialog, <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.Container%2A> always returns a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).

  • ISite.DesignMode

    bool System.ComponentModel.ISite.DesignMode { get; }

Otherwise, <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.IServiceProvider.GetService%2A> returns a null reference (Nothing).
